cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification and optimization of the imaging device, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization aspect also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as gradient descent, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of an optical model, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
